data.title: Amiri Engineering
data.text:
Construction of nine (9) story medical tower, including basement, began in 2019 and will be completed in 2021. Total of 27,000+ cubic yards of concrete were used for the superstructure and Caisson foundation. Construction costs of $150,000,000.

Ten (10) story structure with 6 and 8 story wings as well as office and manufacturing. Photograph of the Adtran project is included in the heading of our website. Amiri Engineering Corporation performed Geotechnical Engineering and Construction Materials Testing services on Phase III construction. Mr. Nasser Amiri was also Project Manager for Geotechnical Engineering and Construction Materials Testing services for Phases I and II. Foundation types installed on this project have included Spread Footings, Caissons, Augercast Piles and Helical Anchor Piles.
